This is a linux service to get tcpdump data in the day range.

INSTALL STEPS:
## 00 Move folder to /opt/tcpdump
sudo su
mv tcpdump /opt/tcpdump

## 01 installl service
sudo chmod 644 *.service
sudo cp *.service /etc/systemd/system
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl start  get_tcpdump_service
sudo systemctl enable get_tcpdump_service

Settings:
Do TCPDUMP in 1800 sec ==> get_tcpdump.sh
Cleanup history 3 days ==> cleanup.sh
